262ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateUniformValue(const Context *context, GLenum valueType, GLenum uniformType)
263{
264 // Check that the value type is compatible with uniform type.
265 // Do the cheaper test first, for a little extra speed.
266 if (valueType != uniformType && VariableBoolVectorType(valueType) != uniformType)
267 {
268 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kUniformSizeMismatch);
269 return false;
270 }
271 return true;
272}

349ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawBase(const Context *context, PrimitiveMode mode)
350{
351 if (!context->getStateCache().isValidDrawMode(mode))
352 {
353 RecordDrawModeError(context, mode);
354 return false;
355 }
356
357 intptr_t drawStatesError = context->getStateCache().getBasicDrawStatesError(context);
358 if (drawStatesError)
359 {
360 const char *errorMessage = reinterpret_cast<const char *>(drawStatesError);
361
362 // All errors from ValidateDrawStates should return INVALID_OPERATION except Framebuffer
363 // Incomplete.
364 bool isFramebufferIncomplete = strcmp(errorMessage, err::kDrawFramebufferIncomplete) == 0;
365 GLenum errorCode =
366 isFramebufferIncomplete ? GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION : GL_INVALID_OPERATION;
367 context->validationError(errorCode, errorMessage);
368 return false;
369 }
370
371 return true;
372}

567ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateVertexFormat(const Context *context,
568 GLuint index,
569 GLint size,
570 VertexAttribTypeCase validation)
571{
572 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
573 if (index >= static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxVertexAttributes))
574 {
575 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kIndexExceedsMaxVertexAttribute);
576 return false;
577 }
578
579 switch (validation)
580 {
581 case VertexAttribTypeCase::Invalid:
582 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, err::kInvalidType);
583 return false;
584 case VertexAttribTypeCase::Valid:
585 if (size < 1 || size > 4)
586 {
587 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kInvalidVertexAttrSize);
588 return false;
589 }
590 break;
591 case VertexAttribTypeCase::ValidSize4Only:
592 if (size != 4)
593 {
594 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
595 err::kInvalidVertexAttribSize2101010);
596 return false;
597 }
598 break;
599 case VertexAttribTypeCase::ValidSize3or4:
600 if (size != 3 && size != 4)
601 {
602 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
603 err::kInvalidVertexAttribSize1010102);
604 return false;
605 }
606 break;
607 }
608
609 return true;
610}

752// Utility macro for handling implementation methods inside Validation.
753#define ANGLE_HANDLE_VALIDATION_ERR(X) \
754 (void)(X); \
755 return false
756#define ANGLE_VALIDATION_TRY(EXPR) ANGLE_TRY_TEMPLATE(EXPR, ANGLE_HANDLE_VALIDATION_ERR)
757
758// We should check with Khronos if returning INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION is OK when querying
759// implementation format info for incomplete framebuffers. It seems like these queries are
760// incongruent with the other errors.
761// Inlined for speed.
762template <GLenum ErrorCode = GL_INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION>
763ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateFramebufferComplete(const Context *context,
764 const Framebuffer *framebuffer)
765{
766 if (!framebuffer->isComplete(context))
767 {
768 context->validationError(ErrorCode, err::kFramebufferIncomplete);
769 return false;
770 }
771
772 return true;
773}

783ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawAttribs(const Context *context, int64_t maxVertex)
784{
785 if (maxVertex > context->getStateCache().getNonInstancedVertexElementLimit())
786 {
787 RecordDrawAttribsError(context);
788 return false;
789 }
790
791 return true;
792}
793
794ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawArraysAttribs(const Context *context, GLint first, GLsizei count, GLsizei primcount)
795{
796 if (!context->isBufferAccessValidationEnabled())
797 {
798 return true;
799 }
800
801 // Check the computation of maxVertex doesn't overflow.
802 // - first < 0 has been checked as an error condition.
803 // - if count <= 0, skip validating no-op draw calls.
804 // From this we know maxVertex will be positive, and only need to check if it overflows GLint.
805 ASSERT(first >= 0);
806 ASSERT(count > 0);
807 int64_t maxVertex = static_cast<int64_t>(first) + static_cast<int64_t>(count) - 1;
808 if (maxVertex > static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<GLint>::max()))
809 {
810 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kIntegerOverflow);
811 return false;
812 }
813
814 if (primcount == 0)
815 {
816 // Skip the specific validation of the non-instanced vertex element limit.
817 return true;
818 }
819
820 return ValidateDrawAttribs(context, maxVertex);
821}
822
823ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawInstancedAttribs(const Context *context, GLint primcount)
824{
825 if (!context->isBufferAccessValidationEnabled())
826 {
827 return true;
828 }
829
830 if ((primcount - 1) > context->getStateCache().getInstancedVertexElementLimit())
831 {
832 RecordDrawAttribsError(context);
833 return false;
834 }
835
836 return true;
837}
838
839ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawArraysCommon(const Context *context,
840 PrimitiveMode mode,
841 GLint first,
842 GLsizei count,
843 GLsizei primcount)
844{
845 if (first < 0)
846 {
847 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kNegativeStart);
848 return false;
849 }
850
851 if (count <= 0)
852 {
853 if (count < 0)
854 {
855 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kNegativeCount);
856 return false;
857 }
858
859 // Early exit.
860 return ValidateDrawBase(context, mode);
861 }
862
863 if (!ValidateDrawBase(context, mode))
864 {
865 return false;
866 }
867
868 if (context->getStateCache().isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
869 {
870 const State &state = context->getState();
871 TransformFeedback *curTransformFeedback = state.getCurrentTransformFeedback();
872 if (!curTransformFeedback->checkBufferSpaceForDraw(count, primcount))
873 {
874 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kTransformFeedbackBufferTooSmall);
875 return false;
876 }
877 }
878
879 return ValidateDrawArraysAttribs(context, first, count, primcount);
880}
881
882ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawElementsBase(const Context *context,
883 PrimitiveMode mode,
884 DrawElementsType type)
885{
886 if (!context->getStateCache().isValidDrawElementsType(type))
887 {
888 if (type == DrawElementsType::UnsignedInt)
889 {
890 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, err::kTypeNotUnsignedShortByte);
891 return false;
892 }
893
894 ASSERT(type == DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum);
895 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, err::kEnumNotSupported);
896 return false;
897 }
898
899 intptr_t drawElementsError = context->getStateCache().getBasicDrawElementsError(context);
900 if (drawElementsError)
901 {
902 // All errors from ValidateDrawElementsStates return INVALID_OPERATION.
903 const char *errorMessage = reinterpret_cast<const char *>(drawElementsError);
904 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, errorMessage);
905 return false;
906 }
907
908 // Note that we are missing overflow checks for active transform feedback buffers.
909 return true;
910}
911
912ANGLE_INLINE bool ValidateDrawElementsCommon(const Context *context,
913 PrimitiveMode mode,
914 GLsizei count,
915 DrawElementsType type,
916 const void *indices,
917 GLsizei primcount)
918{
919 if (!ValidateDrawElementsBase(context, mode, type))
920 {
921 return false;
922 }
923
924 ASSERT(isPow2(GetDrawElementsTypeSize(type)) && GetDrawElementsTypeSize(type) > 0);
925
926 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
927 {
928 GLuint typeBytes = GetDrawElementsTypeSize(type);
929
930 if ((reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(indices) & static_cast<uintptr_t>(typeBytes - 1)) != 0)
931 {
932 // [WebGL 1.0] Section 6.4 Buffer Offset and Stride Requirements
933 // The offset arguments to drawElements and [...], must be a multiple of the size of the
934 // data type passed to the call, or an INVALID_OPERATION error is generated.
935 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kOffsetMustBeMultipleOfType);
936 return false;
937 }
938
939 // [WebGL 1.0] Section 6.4 Buffer Offset and Stride Requirements
940 // In addition the offset argument to drawElements must be non-negative or an INVALID_VALUE
941 // error is generated.
942 if (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(indices) < 0)
943 {
944 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kNegativeOffset);
945 return false;
946 }
947 }
948
949 if (count <= 0)
950 {
951 if (count < 0)
952 {
953 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, err::kNegativeCount);
954 return false;
955 }
956
957 // Early exit.
958 return ValidateDrawBase(context, mode);
959 }
960
961 if (!ValidateDrawBase(context, mode))
962 {
963 return false;
964 }
965
966 const State &state = context->getState();
967 const VertexArray *vao = state.getVertexArray();
968 Buffer *elementArrayBuffer = vao->getElementArrayBuffer();
969
970 if (!elementArrayBuffer)
971 {
972 if (!indices)
973 {
974 // This is an application error that would normally result in a crash, but we catch
975 // it and return an error
976 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kElementArrayNoBufferOrPointer);
977 return false;
978 }
979 }
980 else
981 {
982 // The max possible type size is 8 and count is on 32 bits so doing the multiplication
983 // in a 64 bit integer is safe. Also we are guaranteed that here count > 0.
984 static_assert(std::is_same<int, GLsizei>::value, "GLsizei isn't the expected type");
985 constexpr uint64_t kMaxTypeSize = 8;
986 constexpr uint64_t kIntMax = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
987 constexpr uint64_t kUint64Max = std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max();
988 static_assert(kIntMax < kUint64Max / kMaxTypeSize, "");
989
990 uint64_t elementCount = static_cast<uint64_t>(count);
991 ASSERT(elementCount > 0 && GetDrawElementsTypeSize(type) <= kMaxTypeSize);
992
993 // Doing the multiplication here is overflow-safe
994 uint64_t elementDataSizeNoOffset = elementCount << GetDrawElementsTypeShift(type);
995
996 // The offset can be any value, check for overflows
997 uint64_t offset = static_cast<uint64_t>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(indices));
998 uint64_t elementDataSizeWithOffset = elementDataSizeNoOffset + offset;
999 if (elementDataSizeWithOffset < elementDataSizeNoOffset)
1000 {
1001 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kIntegerOverflow);
1002 return false;
1003 }
1004
1005 // Related to possible test bug: https://github.com/KhronosGroup/WebGL/issues/3064
1006 if ((elementDataSizeWithOffset > static_cast<uint64_t>(elementArrayBuffer->getSize())) &&
1007 (primcount > 0))
1008 {
1009 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kInsufficientBufferSize);
1010 return false;
1011 }
1012 }
1013
1014 if (context->isBufferAccessValidationEnabled() && primcount > 0)
1015 {
1016 // Use the parameter buffer to retrieve and cache the index range.
1017 IndexRange indexRange{IndexRange::Undefined()};
1018 ANGLE_VALIDATION_TRY(vao->getIndexRange(context, type, count, indices, &indexRange));
1019
1020 // If we use an index greater than our maximum supported index range, return an error.
1021 // The ES3 spec does not specify behaviour here, it is undefined, but ANGLE should
1022 // always return an error if possible here.
1023 if (static_cast<GLint64>(indexRange.end) >= context->getCaps().maxElementIndex)
1024 {
1025 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kExceedsMaxElement);
1026 return false;
1027 }
1028
1029 if (!ValidateDrawAttribs(context, static_cast<GLint>(indexRange.end)))
1030 {
1031 return false;
1032 }
1033
1034 // No op if there are no real indices in the index data (all are primitive restart).
1035 return (indexRange.vertexIndexCount > 0);
1036 }
1037
1038 return true;
1039}
1040} // namespace gl
